snippet.title: Exterior Angle Theorem (High School EAT) | Two Opposite Interior Angles Add to the Exterior Angle
snippet.description: http://tapintoteenminds.com Learn why the (High School) Exterior Angle Theorem (EAT) states that any exterior angle of a triangle is equal to the sum of the two opposite interior angles in the same triangle.  Check out the derivation through a visual proof that avoids the use of algebra or complex mathematics.
